  "texts": [
    "Pseudotime inference requires the initial state to be specified.",
    "If the initial state is not known, CytoTRACE 18 can be used to infer a stemness score by assuming that, on average, naive cells express more genes than mature cells.",
    "We found this assumption to be effective for many early developmental scenarios, but, critically, CytoTRACE does not scale in time and memory usage when applied to large datasets and does not resolve individual trajectories through terminal states and fate probabilities (Extended Data Fig. 2b).",
    "We thus developed the CytoTRACEKernel by revising the original CytoTRACE approach, such that edges of k-nearest-neighbor graphs point toward increasing maturity and quantify cell-cell transition probabilities on atlas-scale datasets (Extended Data Fig. 4a and Methods).",
    "Results from our kernel agree with the original approach across multiple datasets (Extended Data Fig. 4b, c and Methods)."
